http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Will-examine-CS%E2%80%99s-absence%E2%80%99/article13991260.ece

Chief Minister Siddaramaiah on Saturday said he would look into the episode surrounding Chief Secretary Arvind Jadhav.Speaking to reporters near Nanjangud after laying foundation stone for development works, the Chief Minister, while replying to queries on the issue over Mr. Jadhav’s absence at MPLAD meeting, said he was not aware of the matter since he was in Mysuru since Friday.“I’ll examine the matter,” he replied, when asked whether the MPs had complained to him over Mr. Jadhav abstaining the meeting. Mr. Jadhav on Friday avoided queries from reporters about his absence at the meeting.